To compute 12 × 34, we can use the standard multiplication method.
\begin{array}{@{}c@{\,}c@{}c@{}c}
& & 1 & 2 \\
& \times & 3 & 4 \\
\cline{2-4}
& & 4 & 8 \\
& 3 & 6 & 0 \\
\cline{2-4}
& 4 & 0 & 8 \\
\end{array}
First, multiply 12 by 4:
12 × 4 = 48. Write down 48.
Next, multiply 12 by 30:
12 × 30 = 360. Write down 360, aligning the 0 with the 8.
Then, add the two results:
48 + 360 = 408.

Alternatively, we can use the distributive property:
12 × 34 = 12 × (30 + 4)
= (12 × 30) + (12 × 4)
= 360 + 48
= 408.

Final Answer: The final answer is $\boxed{408}$
